      "description": "This handscroll depicts a range of tree-covered mountains shrouded in mist. A title written by the artist precedes the painting; the title is a line from a 1936 poem by Mao Zedong and reads \"Jiangshan ruci dou jiao\". It can be translated as \"What a Glorious Land!\", though it is also translated as \"This land, so rich in beauty.\"",
